).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="183" type="a brief historical account">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="183">A brief historical account.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="1979" class="Diplopoda" family="Megalotylidae" genus="Nepalella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nepalella" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Nepalella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shear, WA" journalOrPublisher="Senckenbergiana biologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="115 - 130" refId="B20" refString="Shear, WA, 1979. Diplopoda from the Nepal Himalayas. Chordeumida with comments on the Asian chordeumid fauna. Senckenbergiana biologica 60 (1-2): 115 - 130" title="Diplopoda from the Nepal Himalayas. Chordeumida with comments on the Asian chordeumid fauna." volume="60" year="1979">Shear (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, based on two new species from Nepal, including characters of the female vulvae (= cyphopods) added to both descriptions. 
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch, SI" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="123 - 127" refId="B4" refString="Golovatch, SI, 1983. Contributions to the millipede fauna of Vietnam (Diplopoda) I. Chordeumatida. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 29 (1-3): 123 - 127" title="Contributions to the millipede fauna of Vietnam (Diplopoda) I. Chordeumatida." volume="29" year="1983">Golovatch (1983)</bibRefCitation>
described a new species from northern Vietnam and, together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1978" class="Diplopoda" family="Megalotylidae" genus="Megalotyla" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megalotyla" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Megalotyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, assigned it to the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1978" class="Diplopoda" family="Megalotylidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megalotylidae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shear, WA" journalOrPublisher="Courier Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="229 - 240" refId="B21" refString="Shear, WA, 1987. Chordeumatid Diplopoda from the Nepal Himalayas, II. Courier Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg 93: 229 - 240" title="Chordeumatid Diplopoda from the Nepal Himalayas, II." volume="93" year="1987">Shear (1987)</bibRefCitation>
added further two new species from Nepal, this time using only male specimens for descriptions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79638" author="Mauries, JP" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="3 - 49" refId="B19" refString="Mauries, JP, 1988. Myriapodes du Nepal. II. Diplopodes craspedosomides nouveaux de l'Himalaya et de la region indo-malaise (Craspedosomidea et Chordeumidea). Revue suisse de Zoologie 96 (1): 3 - 49, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79638" title="Myriapodes du Nepal. II. Diplopodes craspedosomides nouveaux de l'Himalaya et de la region indo-malaise (Craspedosomidea et Chordeumidea)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79638" volume="96" year="1988">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mauriès">Mauries</normalizedToken>
(1988)
</bibRefCitation>
published ten new 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="1979" class="Diplopoda" family="Megalotylidae" genus="Nepalella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nepalella" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Nepalella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from Nepal, Myanmar or Thailand, including descriptions of female genitalia that followed 
<bibRefCitation author="Shear, WA" journalOrPublisher="Senckenbergiana biologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="115 - 130" refId="B20" refString="Shear, WA, 1979. Diplopoda from the Nepal Himalayas. Chordeumida with comments on the Asian chordeumid fauna. Senckenbergiana biologica 60 (1-2): 115 - 130" title="Diplopoda from the Nepal Himalayas. Chordeumida with comments on the Asian chordeumid fauna." volume="60" year="1979">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Shear’s">Shear's</normalizedToken>
(1979)
</bibRefCitation>
pattern. Although the morphological differences in the vulvae were often found species-specific, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79638" author="Mauries, JP" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="3 - 49" refId="B19" refString="Mauries, JP, 1988. Myriapodes du Nepal. II. Diplopodes craspedosomides nouveaux de l'Himalaya et de la region indo-malaise (Craspedosomidea et Chordeumidea). Revue suisse de Zoologie 96 (1): 3 - 49, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79638" title="Myriapodes du Nepal. II. Diplopodes craspedosomides nouveaux de l'Himalaya et de la region indo-malaise (Craspedosomidea et Chordeumidea)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79638" volume="96" year="1988">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mauriès">Mauries</normalizedToken>
(1988)
</bibRefCitation>
preferred not to describe new species based solely on female material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
<bibRefCitation author="Shear, WA" journalOrPublisher="Myriapodologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="1 - 10" refId="B22" refString="Shear, WA, 1999. A new troglobitic milliped of the genus Nepalella from China (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida, Megalotylidae). Myriapodologica 6 (1): 1 - 10" title="A new troglobitic milliped of the genus Nepalella from China (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida, Megalotylidae)." volume="6" year="1999">Shear (1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Shear, WA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="63 - 72" refId="B23" refString="Shear, WA, 2002. Five new chordeumatidan millipeds from China: new species of Vieteuma (Kashmireumatidae) and Nepalella (Megalotylidae). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 53 (6): 63 - 72" title="Five new chordeumatidan millipeds from China: new species of Vieteuma (Kashmireumatidae) and Nepalella (Megalotylidae)." volume="53" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
) reviewed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="1979" class="Diplopoda" family="Megalotylidae" genus="Nepalella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nepalella" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Nepalella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and described five new species from China, including 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. magna" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">N. magna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the first to be named based on four female specimens alone. That species was particularly large in size, showed morphologically distinctive vulvae, and found coexisting in syntopy with both 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. griswoldi" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="griswoldi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">N. griswoldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="2002" class="Diplopoda" family="Kashmireumatidae" genus="Vieteuma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Vieteuma longi" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Vieteuma longi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Shear, 2002, the latter taxon another chordeumatidan genus and family (
<bibRefCitation author="Shear, WA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="63 - 72" refId="B23" refString="Shear, WA, 2002. Five new chordeumatidan millipeds from China: new species of Vieteuma (Kashmireumatidae) and Nepalella (Megalotylidae). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 53 (6): 63 - 72" title="Five new chordeumatidan millipeds from China: new species of Vieteuma (Kashmireumatidae) and Nepalella (Megalotylidae)." volume="53" year="2002">Shear 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch, SI" journalOrPublisher="Zoosystema" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="75 - 92" refId="B8" refString="Golovatch, SI, Geoffroy, JJ, Mauries, JP, 2006a. Four new Chordeumatida (Diplopoda) from caves in China. Zoosystema 28 (1): 75 - 92" title="Four new Chordeumatida (Diplopoda) from caves in China." volume="28" year="2006 a">Golovatch et al. (2006a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch, SI" journalOrPublisher="Arthropoda Selecta" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="81 - 89" refId="B9" refString="Golovatch, SI, Geoffroy, JJ, Mauries, JP, 2006b. Several new or poorly-known cavernicolous millipedes (Diplopoda) from southern China. Arthropoda Selecta 15 (2): 81 - 89" title="Several new or poorly-known cavernicolous millipedes (Diplopoda) from southern China." volume="15" year="2006 b">b</bibRefCitation>
) described a further three 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="1979" class="Diplopoda" family="Megalotylidae" genus="Nepalella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nepalella" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Nepalella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Chinese caves and provided a key to all species then known in the genus. More recently, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4243.3.3" author="Liu, W" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" pagination="455 - 482" refId="B18" refString="Liu, W, Wesener, T, Golovatch, SI, Tian, M, 2017b. Contributions to the millipede genus Nepalella Shear, 1979 from China, with four new species and first results on phylogeny based on DNA-barcoding (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida, Megalotylidae). Zootaxa 4243 (3): 455 - 482, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4243.3.3" title="Contributions to the millipede genus Nepalella Shear, 1979 from China, with four new species and first results on phylogeny based on DNA-barcoding (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida, Megalotylidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4243.3.3" volume="4243" year="2017 b">Liu et al. (2017b)</bibRefCitation>
published four new species and two new records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="1979" class="Diplopoda" family="Megalotylidae" genus="Nepalella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nepalella" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Nepalella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including a key to, and a distribution map for, all 12 species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="1979" class="Diplopoda" family="Megalotylidae" genus="Nepalella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nepalella" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Nepalella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from China. This latter study also pioneered barcoding in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="1979" class="Diplopoda" family="Megalotylidae" genus="Nepalella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nepalella" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Nepalella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, providing the first molecular-based phylogeny of a chordeumatidan genus outside Europe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
